《[[星際大戰四部曲：曙光乍現|星球大战]]》意外热卖并成为文化现象级电影，续集马上提上日程<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|2–3}}<ref>{{cite web | last = Bova | first = Ben | title = Why Hollywood finds profits out of this world | date = 1977-11-13 | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029070028/https://www.nytimes.com/1977/11/13/archives/why-hollywood-finds-profits-out-of-this-world-science-fiction.html | website = The New York Times | dead-url = no | page = D1 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1977/11/13/archives/why-hollywood-finds-profits-out-of-this-world-science-fiction.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Kennedy | first = Harlan | title = Another film that's out of this world | website = The New York Times | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1979/02/18/archives/another-film-thats-out-of-this-world.html | date = 1979-02-18 | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | dead-url = no | page = D15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029070615/https://www.nytimes.com/1979/02/18/archives/another-film-thats-out-of-this-world.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Higham | first = Charles | title = What makes Alan Ladd Jr. Hollywood's hottest producer? | website = The New York Times | date = 1977-07-17 | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029064245/https://www.nytimes.com/1977/07/17/archives/what-makes-alan-ladd-jr-hollywoods-hottest-producer.html | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | dead-url = no | page = 61 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1977/07/17/archives/what-makes-alan-ladd-jr-hollywoods-hottest-producer.html }}</ref>。主创人[[乔治·卢卡斯|乔治·卢卡斯]]预留后路，万一《星球大战》票房失利就请[[亚伦·迪恩·佛斯特|亚伦·迪恩·佛斯特]]编写低成本续集剧本（后改编成小说《[[心灵之眼的碎片|心灵之眼的碎片]]》发行）<ref name="DOGBrackett">{{cite web | first = John | last = Saavedra | url = https://www.denofgeek.com/movies/star-wars-the-empire-strikes-back-leigh-brackett/ | title = Star Wars: Leigh Brackett and The Empire Strikes Back you never saw | access-date = 2022-01-23 | website = Den of Geek | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211021104711/https://www.denofgeek.com/movies/star-wars-the-empire-strikes-back-leigh-brackett/ | archive-date = 2021-10-21 | dead-url = no | date = 2019-05-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Wenz | first = John | title = The first Star Wars sequel: Inside the writing of Splinter of the Mind's Eye | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129173123/https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/the-first-star-wars-sequel-inside-the-writing-of-splinter-of-the-minds-eye | access-date = 2020-11-29 | archive-date = 2020-11-29 | date = 2018-01-01 | website = Syfy | url = https://syfy.com/syfywire/the-first-star-wars-sequel-inside-the-writing-of-splinter-of-the-minds-eye }}</ref>。电影大卖已成定局之际，卢卡斯又觉得当导演压力太大，影响身体健康，不愿再执导续集<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="NYTimesROTJ">{{cite web | last = Bock | first = Audie | title = Secrecy shrouds a 'Star Wars' sequel | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1982/07/11/movies/moviesspecial/secrecy-shrouds-a-star-wars-sequel.html | website = The New York Times | date = 1982-07-11 | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029073028/https://www.nytimes.com/1982/07/11/movies/moviesspecial/secrecy-shrouds-a-star-wars-sequel.html | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|2–4}}。电影为卢卡斯带来财富与名望，也有许多人只想得到他的经济支持，为此甚至诉诸威胁<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|2–3}}。

卢卡斯深知续集必然在耗资等各方面超越原作，但自创的[[卢卡斯影业|卢卡斯影业]]规模太小，连办公室都是临时的，考虑把项目转卖[[二十世紀影業|二十世纪福克斯]]换取利润分成<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="NYTimesROTJ" /><ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|3}}。《星球大战》令他进账颇丰，短期内根本不需要工作赚钱，但在创作上已投入太多心血，无法将其托付他人<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|4}}<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="NYTimesROTJ" /><ref name="NYTimesKurtz">{{cite web | last = Lewin | first = David | title = Can the makers of ''Star Wars'' do it again? | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1979/12/02/archives/can-the-makers-of-star-wars-do-it-again.html | website = The New York Times | date = 1979-12-02 | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029071026/https://www.nytimes.com/1979/12/02/archives/can-the-makers-of-star-wars-do-it-again.html }}</ref>。他对续集已有构想，但还没有完整结构<ref name="DOGBrackett" />，知道剧情会更阴暗，对主题、人物关系、原力本质的探索更成熟<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" />。卢卡斯打算用《星球大战》所赚1200万美元利润独立制作续集，扩张旗下特效公司[[光影魔幻工業|光影魔幻工業]]，在加利福尼亚州[[马林县_(加利福尼亚州)|马林县]]创立[[天行者牧场|天行者]][[电影牧场|电影牧场]]，用剩余资产抵押，从[[美國銀行|美國銀行]]贷款八百万美元作为预算<ref name="NYTimesKurtz" /><ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="Hearn-2005">{{Cite book | first = Marcus | last = Hearn | title = The Cinema of George Lucas | url = https://archive.org/details/cinemageorgeluca00hear | publisher = H. N. Abrams |year=2005 | location = New York City | isbn = 978-0-8109-4968-3 | access-date = 2022-01-23}}</ref>{{rp|123–124}}<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|10,30–31, 52, 53}}。

福克斯有权率先协商或拒绝参与《星球大战》续作，该司与卢卡斯各派代表从1977年中期开始谈判。福克斯此前认为《星球大战》上映后必然惨淡收场，项目分文不值，同意卢卡斯主控周边商品和续作开发。<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|4}}公司高管[[艾伦·拉德二世|艾伦·拉德二世]]一直支持《星球大战》，非常希望尽早推出续集，受其影响双方在续集条款达成共识的速度远超前作<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|10,190}}。1977年9月21日双方签订百页合同，福克斯负责发行但无权干涉电影创作，换取前两千万毛利的一半，如果毛利超出一亿美元，制片方分成将提升至77.5%。电影必须在1979年1月结束前开拍，1980年5月1日上映。<ref name="NYTimesKurtz" /><ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|10,11}}合约为卢卡斯提供丰厚利润空间，但要是票房惨败，他也会血本无归<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="Hearn-2005" />{{rp|124}}。

卢卡斯为减轻风险创办“第二章公司”，控制项目开发并分担责任<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|10,30}}。他为新公司与卢卡斯影业签订合同，分走半成票房毛利<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|58}}。他还创办“黑隼”为《星球大战》商品营销授权，收益投入开发项目<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|54}}。1977年8月项目开始开发，暂定名《星球大战第二章》<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|7}}。

卢卡斯得知[[加里·库尔茨|加里·库尔茨]]在《星球大战》拍摄期间一度玩乎职守，放任遇到的问题不管，打算改请[[霍华德·卡赞强|霍华德·卡赞强]]制片，但考虑到库尔兹多年来对他忠心耿耿而且很了解《星球大战》系列而改变心意<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|34–35}}。卢卡斯担任执行制片人，能抽时间应对《[[法櫃奇兵|法櫃奇兵]]》项目开发等事务<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="NYTimesKurtz" /><ref name="Hearn-2005" />{{rp|122}}。库尔茨1977年结束前就聘请美术总监诺曼·雷诺兹、布景顾问[[约翰·巴里_(布景)|约翰·巴里]]、化妆师[[斯图尔特·弗里伯恩|斯图尔特·弗里伯恩]]、第一副导演[[大卫·汤布林|大卫·汤布林]]等主要剧组人员<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|11,51}}，卢卡斯再度邀请[[拉尔夫·麦克奎里|拉尔夫·麦克奎里]]与[[喬·約翰斯頓|喬·約翰斯頓]]，确保续集视觉风格与原作一致，三人同年12月开始构想冰雪行星霍斯的大战<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|12,31}}。电影预算此时已升至千万美元<ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|30}}。卢卡斯决定请他人执导，希望此人支持他的构想，而且同意卢卡斯掌握决定权<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" />。他一度考虑[[亞倫·帕克|亞倫·帕克]]、[[约翰·班德汉姆|约翰·班德汉姆]]等近百名导演，最后在1978年2月拍板老相识[[爾文·克許納|爾文·克許納]]<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="Rinzler-2010" />{{rp|34}}。克什纳不大愿意为《星球大战》这样的热门巨作拍续集，朋友也劝他不要接受，万一票房惨败难免受千夫所指<ref name="EmpireMakingOf" /><ref name="Buckley-1980" />。卢卡斯表示《星球大战》系列有更宏大的结构，本片与其说是续集，不如与原作一样看成其中章节，还承诺克什纳可以按自有构想拍摄<ref name="Buckley-1980">{{cite news | last = Buckley | first = Tom | date = 1980-05-16 | title = At the Movies; The 'Force' behind ''Empire Strikes Back''. | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1980/05/16/archives/at-the-movies-the-force-behind-empire-strikes-back.html | page = C13 | work = The New York Times | location = New York | access-date = 2022-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211029071129/https://www.nytimes.com/1980/05/16/archives/at-the-movies-the-force-behind-empire-strikes-back.html | archive-date = 2021-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 编剧 ===
